node.text:
Huge thank you to the rescuers in this video 💚 Unfortunately not all turtles are this lucky. Once trapped in a net, turtles are dragged through the water with no access to the surface to breathe, causing them to drown. It's estimated that some 4,600 sea turtles are killed by fishing nets and hooks every year in U.S. waters alone ☹️
Video via @thedodo

node.text:
How would you react? 😳🐍
Video by @brodiemoss

"Sea snakes normally avoid humans but this time of year they become very active, sexually frustrated and potentially aggressive as they search for a mate 🐍 like this old fella who appeared from the ocean floor and followed me around on my paddle board before disappearing" 😅

node.text:
Turtle cleaning! 🛀 🏝 Why is this done?
A build up of algae and other waste can lead to skin disease so it’s important that we clean their shells often! 
The brown and green on the turtles are a mix of algae and water scales. ***This turtle is being cleaned at a marine rescue centre / do not try this!! In the wild this is done by cleaner fish 🐟
~
Video by @ogasawara_marine_centre

node.text:
"Sometimes baby humpback whales get a little excited. Here is a humpack whale the length of a camper van flying at me like a torpedo.
We spent a long time with this one who would play and breach around us while her mother rested down below.
As calves they can sense and will feed off your energy, and similar to puppies you can play calmly, or you can get them riled up. If the mother is ok with it, I like to get them excited. By the end of it, she was a bit too comfortable around me." 
Caption + Video By @karimiliya

Absolutely mind-blowing clarity 🤯⁣
🌊🎥: @nolanomura 🤙⁣⁣
Music:⁣⁣⁣⁣
1) @pinksweats 🎵⁣⁣⁣⁣
2) Talking Slow @dylanjordan 🎵⁣⁣
-⁣
Tag someone that should see this!

node.text:
Helpless turtle gets rescued ❤️🙌🏼

Join Brodie Moss and the crew as they explore the remote islands of Australia. This time of year brings in hundreds of mating turtles to the shallows. Right place at the right time allowed the crew to rescue a washed up helpless turtle stuck on her back.

📽 @brodiemoss
🎶 Julius Dreisig & Zeus X Crona - Invisible provided by NoCopyrightSounds

node.text:
Spotting the rare pink dolphin 🐬💖

While we’re not sure whether this video was edited or not, pink dolphins actually exist. The endangered Amazon river dolphin and Indo-Pacific humpback dolphin both have a pink shade to them (especially males). Have you heard of them before?

via @discoverwildlife
